From a130bf623e4fcac9e296bd8b8e8c4d7b2b425233 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Mazzitelli <mazz@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 13 Apr 2021 09:19:08 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Backport changes to v1.24 (#286)

* Abort on ad hoc kiali namespace deployment when it is not allowed (#278)

* 1.33.0 manifests

* OLM metadata - add the new ALLOW_AD_HOC_KIALI_NAMESPACE env var. Set it to false by default since that is more secure for multi-tenant scenarios

* Abort on ad hoc kiali namespace deployment when it is not allowed.

This fails the reconciliation if user tries to install kiali in a namespace different from where the CR is. This failure only happens when the Operator is configured to disallow such a thing (which is going to be the default).

* get molecule tests to pass with the new setting

* for backward compatibility, keep this set to true since that was how it worked before. Admins can set this to "false" if they want to disallow ad-hoc namespace installations

* backport the new feature in the 1.12 and 1.24 roles

(cherry picked from commit 8e5d04d8485284376e9e66fcd51d0be46b4dc06e)

* by default, don't allow ad-hoc namespaces (#280)

* by default, don't allow ad-hoc namespaces

* fix formatting so the ad-hoc namespace check works in v1.24 and v1.12 playbooks

(cherry picked from commit ef176e2ac209d6aba0403d06bce5c7641d6826ff)

* retain the permissions that are still needed for the old supported versions (#281)

fixes: https://github.com/kiali/kiali/issues/3854
(cherry picked from commit 1d0c4c67c278c035adf38a8f294d738fc278f735)

* Remove support for v1.0 (#282)

fixes: https://github.com/kiali/kiali/issues/3351
(cherry picked from commit 6ad8ada2026c477f4a714314a399e09e4ede6897)

* Be able to disable ad hoc images. (#284)

fixes: https://github.com/kiali/kiali/issues/3865
(cherry picked from commit cff4c37fe29c3997a897e0a969ceb27b3236570c)

* remove .travis.yml
